<TITLE> Bhuiyan to roll out final reform proposals at 4pm </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 12 (bdnews24.com)  BNP secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan will announce a `complete reform proposal' at 4:00pmThursday at his Gulshan home, BNP joint secretary general Ashraf Hossain said. The proposal bars a person from holding the office of secretary general for more than two consecutive terms. Bhuiyan discussed reforms with former BNP lawmakers and district leaders of Chittagong Division in morning. He advised the former lawmakers to talk to the grassroots leaders about the upcoming council meeting. ZA Khan, adviser to the chairperson, former lawmaker Jafrul Islam Chowdhury, Manirul Haque Chowdhury, Gias Quader Chowdhury, Joynal Abedin, Mosharaf Hossain, Shahiduzzaman and leaders from Chandpur and Cox's Bazar districts were also present there. "We are taking preparation for the council. We will meet the chairperson as soon as possible for seeking her permission for the council. "We hope, considering the present situation, the chairperson will give permission for the national council," Ashraf told reporters at Bhuiyan's home. On June 25, Bhuiyan announced a draft proposal that said the party chairperson could not hold office for more than two terms on the trot. This time he is set to make some proposals about parliament, Election Commission, administration and economic affairs, sources familiar with the reform process said. bdnews24
